    "body": "### Problem\n\n`nvim_open_win()` does not seem to support comma-separated string values for the `border` option. For the `border` option, the docs for `nvim_open_win()` mention that `The string form accepts the same values as the 'winborder' option.` which leads me to believe this is a bug since the introduction of custom `'winborder'` characters (#33772).\n\nA failing test:\n\n```diff\ndiff --git a/test/functional/ui/float_spec.lua b/test/functional/ui/float_spec.lua\nindex 9eb2b750f2..b5e38de87d 100644\n--- a/test/functional/ui/float_spec.lua\n+++ b/test/functional/ui/float_spec.lua\n@@ -10958,6 +10958,12 @@ describe('float window', function()\n       eq('Vim(set):E474: Invalid argument: winborder=+,-,+,|,+,-,+,', pcall_err(command, [[set winborder=+,-,+,\\|,+,-,+,]]))\n       eq('Vim(set):E474: Invalid argument: winborder=custom', pcall_err(command, 'set winborder=custom'))\n     end)\n+\n+    it('no error with comma-separated string border value', function()\n+      local buf = api.nvim_create_buf(false, false)\n+      local config = { relative = 'editor', width = 4, height = 4, row = 2, col = 2, border = '+,-,+,|,+,-,+,' }\n+      api.nvim_open_win(buf, true, config)\n+    end)\n   end\n \n   describe('with ext_multigrid', function()\n\n```\n\nTest output:\n\n```\nERROR    test/functional/ui/float_spec.lua @ 10962: float window with ext_multigrid no error with comma-separated string border value\ntest/functional/testnvim.lua:139: invalid border style \"+,-,+,|,+,-,+,\"\n\nstack traceback:\n        test/functional/testnvim.lua:139: in function 'nvim_open_win'\n        test/functional/ui/float_spec.lua:10965: in function <test/functional/ui/float_spec.lua:10962>\n```\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```\n$ git apply <<'EOF'\ndiff --git a/test/functional/ui/float_spec.lua b/test/functional/ui/float_spec.lua\nindex 9eb2b750f2..b5e38de87d 100644\n--- a/test/functional/ui/float_spec.lua\n+++ b/test/functional/ui/float_spec.lua\n@@ -10958,6 +10958,12 @@ describe('float window', function()\n       eq('Vim(set):E474: Invalid argument: winborder=+,-,+,|,+,-,+,', pcall_err(command, [[set winborder=+,-,+,\\|,+,-,+,]]))\n       eq('Vim(set):E474: Invalid argument: winborder=custom', pcall_err(command, 'set winborder=custom'))\n     end)\n+\n+    it('no error with comma-separated string border value', function()\n+      local buf = api.nvim_create_buf(false, false)\n+      local config = { relative = 'editor', width = 4, height = 4, row = 2, col = 2, border = '+,-,+,|,+,-,+,' }\n+      api.nvim_open_win(buf, true, config)\n+    end)\n   end\n \n   describe('with ext_multigrid', function()\nEOF\n\n$ FILE=test/functional/ui/float_spec.lua make functionaltest\n```\n\nor\n\n```lua\nlocal api = vim.api\napi.nvim_open_win(api.nvim_create_buf(false, true), true, {\n    border = \"+,-,+,|,+,-,+,|\",\n    row = 1,\n    col = 1,\n    width = 100,\n    height = 100,\n    relative = \"editor\",\n})\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`nvim_open_win()` to support comma-separated string `border` values, similar to `'winborder'` and as mentioned in the docs.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0 commit e512efe3696b2ed18db55683fecf42bbc733c767\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 15.5\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.42.2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
